## Conventions
- Internal HTTPS targets use self-signed certs ‚Äî `curl -sk` is expected.
- Probe commands should carry a short `--max-time`/`--connect-timeout`.
- **MCP servers** follow one homing convention ‚Äî server lives with its
  capability (`<project>/<project>_mcp_server.py`), one client plane, secrets
  from `~/.key`, any network-listening server binds the LAN IP with a bearer.
  Full convention + the served/consumed inventory: `cc-skills/MCP.md`.
